1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:01,870
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,870 --> 00:00:03,610
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:05,480
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,180 --> 00:00:10,280
Before this night is over,
I need to return something to you.

5
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:22,190
Yu Na, my goodness!
What do you think you're doing?

6
00:00:23,130 --> 00:00:24,130
You...

7
00:00:25,830 --> 00:00:27,070
What was that?

8
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:32,400
That's what you get
for breaking our promise.

9
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:36,780
We promised to be friends,
to be on the same side...

10
00:00:36,780 --> 00:00:38,080
and you played dirty.

11
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:40,310
I can't just let that slide, can I?

12
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:44,150
Since you stabbed me in the back,

13
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:46,790
I had to
at least slap you in the face.

14
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:56,590
How dare you mess with my son?

15
00:00:58,330 --> 00:00:59,330
Why not?

16
00:01:00,670 --> 00:01:02,730
You get to go after my son,

17
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,270
but I'm not allowed
to go after yours?

18
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:09,040
If you were set on trapping my son
in an unhappy marriage,

19
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:13,040
you should've known your own son
could end up miserable too.

20
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:16,280
If anything happens to Min Jun,

21
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:19,320
the same thing will happen
to your son.

22
00:01:20,820 --> 00:01:23,050
He'll pay the price
for having a mother like you.

23
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:28,590
Don't think you've won.

24
00:01:32,460 --> 00:01:36,400
You'll pay tenfold
for humiliating me today,

25
00:01:38,370 --> 00:01:39,940
and I'll get even...

26
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:43,580
for Hyun Jun too.

27
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:54,950
(Gemologist Kim Myung Hui
Says the Ornament Is Fake)

28
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:58,220
(Park Tae Ho)

29
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,080
Right.

30
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:24,850
Excuse me. Just a second.

31
00:02:25,850 --> 00:02:26,850
What is it?

32
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:29,650
Is this...

33
00:02:30,420 --> 00:02:32,260
where Kim Dan Hui lives?

34
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:34,830
There's no one by that name here.

35
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:36,190
- Leave.
- No, wait.

36
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:38,700
- Just leave.
- Hold on.

37
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:39,960
Yes, sir.

38
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:42,530
Who?

39
00:02:43,170 --> 00:02:45,170
Who is Kim Dan Hui,

40
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,570
and who are you? Let's start there.

41
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,080
Oh, right.

42
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:56,610
Kim Dan Hui is
my late uncle's daughter.

43
00:02:57,250 --> 00:03:00,180
Actually, she was adopted...

44
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,590
- and I'm...
- Sir!

45
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:06,990
Now they're showing up
right at your doorstep.

46
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:09,960
- Secretary Jung, do you know him?
- Yes.

47
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:13,870
We've had many people stopping by
to complain about appraisals lately.

48
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:17,700
They're demanding compensation,
making ridiculous threats.

49
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:20,270
Sir, please don't worry
and head inside.

50
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:21,670
This is ridiculous?

51
00:03:21,940 --> 00:03:23,610
Nonsense? Threats?

52
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:26,680
Look here, mister. We'll talk alone.

53
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:29,880
- I'll handle this.
- You're a joke, lady.

54
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:31,280
- Talk to me.
- No, the chairman...

55
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:33,920
- Come on. We'll talk alone.
- That hurts.

56
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:49,670
What...

57
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:53,170
Why are you two at it again?

58
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:55,170
Honey.

59
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,810
- That Kim Myung Hui...
- What?

60
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:05,150
Ms. Oh has caused a problem.

61
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:06,880
A problem?

62
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,890
I wouldn't call it a problem.

63
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:17,630
She interfered
with the competition you ordered.

64
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:21,100
She and Ms. Choi threatened
Producer Shin and as a result,

65
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:24,470
Chloe never even got
to meet with him.

66
00:04:24,970 --> 00:04:25,970
What?

67
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:29,970
You teamed up with Ms. Choi again
and defied my orders?

68
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:34,150
I didn't have a choice.

69
00:04:36,410 --> 00:04:39,150
You shouldn't have let Hyun Jun
get involved with that vixen.

70
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:42,320
If you'd shut them down,
I wouldn't have had to get involved!

71
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:46,920
I will never let our Hyun Jun marry
that little vixen.

72
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,990
What gives you the right
to raise your voice?

73
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:52,560
Chloe has been put at a disadvantage
because of this.

74
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:56,200
As it stands,
we can't call this competition fair.

75
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:58,670
You'll need to sort this out, sir.

76
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:05,480
All right.
Bring in Ms. Choi and Chloe!

77
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:08,780
Darn.

78
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,860
I'd say this makes us even,

79
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,030
and since our deal is still on,

80
00:05:29,330 --> 00:05:31,400
let's get back on the same side
starting tomorrow.

81
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:34,540
The same side?

82
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,340
Are you out of your mind?

83
00:05:39,410 --> 00:05:44,150
Honey. My goodness, are you awake?

84
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:45,580
Honey.

85
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:50,090
Oh no, what's wrong? Honey!

86
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:53,420
My goodness, you're fading again?

87
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:55,560
She's not Jin Ju.

88
00:05:55,660 --> 00:05:56,690
Honey.

89
00:06:00,030 --> 00:06:01,530
Honey, honestly...

90
00:06:01,970 --> 00:06:03,700
Yes. What's this about?

91
00:06:06,070 --> 00:06:07,070
Right now?

92
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,370
All right. I'm on my way.

93
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:18,520
Chairman Park is probably
calling you in.

94
00:06:19,820 --> 00:06:22,290
What? Why would he...

95
00:06:23,450 --> 00:06:26,220
If I found out,
I'm sure the Chairman did too.

96
00:06:27,730 --> 00:06:31,200
About what you and his wife
were up to.

97
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,610
I told you to compete,

98
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,940
not resort to threats
or meddling with contracts.

99
00:06:49,410 --> 00:06:52,750
It's a competition,
so you have to win by any means.

100
00:06:53,620 --> 00:06:56,750
I just chose a more direct method
to secure the contract.

101
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,190
Exactly.

102
00:06:58,490 --> 00:07:00,890
Once you're in a fight,
winning is all that matters.

103
00:07:01,030 --> 00:07:02,430
How can you two...

104
00:07:02,430 --> 00:07:03,800
They're right.

105
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:08,430
To marry into the Adele Group,
you need to be that vicious.

106
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,970
You have to be willing
to betray your friends,

107
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:15,170
be shameless in your wickedness,

108
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:20,380
and ruin a life
without batting an eye.

109
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:25,880
I was too naive.

110
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,520
If you tell me to stop here,
I will accept your decision.

111
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,260
Chloe.

112
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:35,290
You'll abide by my decision?

113
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:37,600
Of course I will.

114
00:07:38,630 --> 00:07:42,070
Because there's no way
you'd ever side with Choi Yu Na.

115
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:47,740
What are you waiting for?
She said she'll accept your choice.

116
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:52,240
Just declare Ms. Choi the winner
and get rid of that vixen.

117
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:54,950
We're choosing a daughter-in-law
for the Adele family.

118
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:57,580
The process itself
must be fair, sir.

119
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:11,760
From the beginning.

120
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:15,100
Start over.

121
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:19,370
- From the beginning...
- Start over?

122
00:08:21,110 --> 00:08:22,470
The Adele Group...

123
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:25,040
must live up to its name
and act with integrity.

124
00:08:26,410 --> 00:08:29,980
If someone like Producer Shin
reported this,

125
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:32,150
how would you handle the fallout?

126
00:08:32,380 --> 00:08:35,520
That man can't press charges.
I've got some serious dirt on him...

127
00:08:37,190 --> 00:08:39,320
To marry into the Adele Group,

128
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:43,660
you have to care
about your public image.

129
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:47,270
I said I'd be judging
based on ability,

130
00:08:47,930 --> 00:08:50,370
not on who could stoop the lowest.

131
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:53,040
You're as wise as ever, sir.

132
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:57,340
Since Ms. Choi had a private meeting
with Producer Shin,

133
00:08:57,640 --> 00:09:01,010
why doesn't Chloe do the same?

134
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:05,750
I have no objection,
but will Producer Shin cooperate?

135
00:09:06,550 --> 00:09:09,020
We'll have to make a formal apology
and ask for his understanding.

136
00:09:09,950 --> 00:09:14,330
You two, apologize to Producer Shin
and clean up this mess.

137
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,060
Apologize?

138
00:09:16,990 --> 00:09:18,300
Why me, too?

139
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:21,830
Would you rather
I just declare Chloe the winner?

140
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:47,430
Darn, my head is killing me.

141
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:49,630
How did everyone find out?

142
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:52,630
This was a done deal.
How did it all fall apart?

143
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:56,130
How will you take responsibility
for this?

144
00:09:57,170 --> 00:09:58,240
Responsibility?

145
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:01,910
If the leak didn't come from me,
it must've been you.

146
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:06,410
How can you be so sure it was me
and not you?

147
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:09,750
No use crying over spilt milk.

148
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,850
Quit fussing
and rewrite the proposal.

149
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:16,590
You think I can just whip one up
out of thin air?

150
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,820
Yes, just change the numbers.

151
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:23,290
Propose a production budget
much higher than before.

152
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:24,860
Actually, no.

153
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:28,670
Offer far more
than that Chloe would.

154
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:31,070
Everyone has a price.

155
00:10:36,110 --> 00:10:37,140
Get going already.

156
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:47,490
I see you've decided to take my side
in the competition.

157
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:51,720
Because if I win,

158
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:54,790
Park Min Jun will be able to escape
that unwanted marriage.

159
00:10:55,660 --> 00:10:57,330
You told me once, didn't you?

160
00:10:57,730 --> 00:11:01,330
Back when the chairman announced
the symbol design competition,

161
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:04,070
that you'd never run
from a challenge...

162
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:06,270
where you had to prove yourself,

163
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,570
and that
you'd never lost one either.

164
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:13,240
Don't lose this time either.

165
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:15,810
This is an opportunity
you fought hard to get back.

166
00:11:16,150 --> 00:11:17,450
I really hope you win.

167
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,580
Sure.

168
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:21,250
I will.

169
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,120
That's what I'm supposed
to say, right?

170
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:26,590
But you're not
really cheering for me.

171
00:11:26,590 --> 00:11:28,730
You're just worried about your son.

172
00:11:41,310 --> 00:11:42,410
Kim Dan Hui.

173
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:50,920
Do you...

174
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,690
know someone named Kim Dan Hui?

175
00:11:58,420 --> 00:12:00,420
What do you mean by that?

176
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:06,030
Someone came by the house
looking for Kim Dan Hui.

177
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,700
Sorry?

178
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:13,340
According to Secretary Jung,
it's about the jewelry appraisal.

179
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:16,640
He was looking for compensation.

180
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:17,910
But then why...

181
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:22,450
was he looking for Kim Dan Hui...

182
00:12:23,350 --> 00:12:24,920
and not Kim Myung Hui?

183
00:12:27,020 --> 00:12:28,020
I'm not sure.

184
00:12:28,950 --> 00:12:30,920
Maybe he got my name wrong.

185
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,590
Right. I suppose...

186
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:40,230
Myung Hui and Dan Hui
do sound alike.

187
00:12:42,830 --> 00:12:47,100
You need to handle complainers
like that decisively.

188
00:12:47,810 --> 00:12:51,110
Don't let them bring office problems
to our home.

189
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,780
Yes, sir. I'll take care of it.

190
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:17,900
My adoptive father's nephew?

191
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:19,700
Apparently.

192
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:24,040
Remember the appraisal issue?
You were on the news because of it.

193
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:26,740
It looks like he recognized you
from the news.

194
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:31,150
Did your adoptive father
actually have a nephew?

195
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:34,120
I vaguely remember him.

196
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:38,160
But I don't think
they were that close.

197
00:13:39,060 --> 00:13:40,490
Why did he show up?

198
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:43,230
- Money.
- Money?

199
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,860
Yes.

200
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:48,270
He said since you married rich,
you have a duty to help him out.

201
00:13:49,430 --> 00:13:52,240
He was raising a stink,
demanding to see you immediately.

202
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:54,840
I got his contact info
and told him we'd be in touch.

203
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:58,580
What are we going to do about him?

204
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,050
Hyun Jun, wait.

205
00:14:06,150 --> 00:14:09,420
Here. You forgot your medicine.

206
00:14:11,860 --> 00:14:12,860
You got stitches,

207
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:15,330
so you really need
to take your antibiotics.

208
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:16,730
I don't need them.

209
00:14:17,430 --> 00:14:18,460
Hyun Jun, hey.

210
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:22,870
You have to take them.
It'll help your hand heal.

211
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:26,170
That's a deep cut.

212
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:28,370
If it gets infected,
it could be serious.

213
00:14:32,410 --> 00:14:33,610
Hyun Jun...

214
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,190
Here.

215
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:50,160
Please give this to Hyun Jun for me.

216
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,500
Sure.

217
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:57,170
Don't worry about it, head inside.

218
00:15:27,330 --> 00:15:30,530
Stop making everyone worry
and just take them.

219
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,270
Mind your own business and get lost.

220
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:45,320
If you're mad at your mother,
take it out on her.

221
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:47,580
Stop making everyone else
uncomfortable.

222
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:50,150
I see.

223
00:15:51,090 --> 00:15:54,220
Was I taking my anger out
on innocent people?

224
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:57,330
Is that it?

225
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:02,570
And I suppose
you've done nothing wrong?

226
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,870
You and your mother...

227
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:11,580
humiliated me in front of Chloe,

228
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:14,480
and I'm the one who's wrong
for being angry?

229
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:17,480
About that...

230
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,080
I'm sorry.

231
00:16:19,150 --> 00:16:21,420
Honestly, just make excuses
or get angry.

232
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:26,020
That's way better than trying
to make me look like the bad guy.

233
00:16:29,330 --> 00:16:30,330
Then again,

234
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,630
this is typical of you.

235
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:35,530
You act like Jin Ju is your world,

236
00:16:35,530 --> 00:16:37,100
but you use her as an excuse...

237
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:39,840
to get close to Chloe
and mess with her.

238
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,470
How dare you go after my woman?

239
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:45,040
You turn it into some epic romance,

240
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:48,450
and I end up
looking like the villain.

241
00:16:51,420 --> 00:16:53,780
Min Jun. Park Min Jun.

242
00:16:54,450 --> 00:16:55,990
If you're really sorry,

243
00:16:55,990 --> 00:16:59,490
then please keep your distance
from me and Chloe!

244
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:03,790
Go back to Baek Jin Ju...

245
00:17:05,430 --> 00:17:07,130
and love her instead.

246
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:14,710
I don't think I'm the only one...

247
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:17,340
using Jin Ju as an excuse.

248
00:17:20,510 --> 00:17:21,550
Don't you ever...

249
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:23,910
drag her into...

250
00:17:25,050 --> 00:17:26,850
what's between me and Chloe again.

251
00:17:59,950 --> 00:18:01,990
You act like Jin Ju is your world,

252
00:18:01,990 --> 00:18:03,620
but you use her as an excuse...

253
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:06,290
to get close to Chloe
and mess with her.

254
00:18:06,290 --> 00:18:08,090
How dare you go after my woman?

255
00:18:09,730 --> 00:18:11,400
You turn it into some epic romance.

256
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:13,330
If you're really sorry,

257
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:17,100
then please keep your distance
from me and Chloe!

258
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:21,170
Go back to Baek Jin Ju...

259
00:18:22,170 --> 00:18:23,770
and love her instead.

260
00:18:32,850 --> 00:18:34,380
Do you think so too?

261
00:18:35,090 --> 00:18:37,020
Am I using you as an excuse again...

262
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:39,260
to hold on to Chloe?

263
00:18:47,130 --> 00:18:49,830
(Personal Fingerprint
Registration Image)

264
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:54,100
Can't you make an exception
just this once?

265
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:57,540
Just this one last time.

266
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:01,750
Is there no way
to be absolutely sure?

267
00:19:17,530 --> 00:19:18,530
Unless...

268
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,030
maybe...

269
00:19:31,210 --> 00:19:33,980
(Adele)

270
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:45,690
What? Why are you butting in?

271
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:50,130
I need to see if you're here
to apologize or sabotage me.

272
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,000
Welcome, Producer Shin.

273
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,900
I'm Chloe Lee.
I'll be running our meeting today.

274
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:02,740
A pleasure to meet you.

275
00:20:03,570 --> 00:20:06,840
First, about that incident
last time...

276
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,680
You deserve an apology.

277
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:24,030
I'm sorry about
what happened last time.

278
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:28,800
Your turn, Ms. Oh.

279
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:30,930
You can be such a pain.

280
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:35,940
Fine, sorry. Happy now?

281
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,450
Your apology says a lot
about who you are.

282
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:45,150
Wasn't saying sorry enough?

283
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:50,420
Look, I said I was sorry,
so don't bother me about it anymore.

284
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:01,730
I came here for an apology,
and I've only been further insulted.

285
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:05,400
I'm so sorry.
Let me apologize for them.

286
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:11,210
But since you're already here,
could you at least hear me out?

287
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,280
I don't have much time.

288
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:14,950
Would ten minutes work?

289
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:16,550
Yes, that's more than enough.

290
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:19,620
Aren't you leaving?

291
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:24,290
I need to see if you're actually
making a proposal...

292
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:26,120
or trying to sabotage me.

293
00:21:32,860 --> 00:21:35,670
The reason
people love your documentaries,

294
00:21:35,830 --> 00:21:38,900
is that they show ways
to stay healthy in everyday life.

295
00:21:39,570 --> 00:21:43,170
Our product was born
from that very same philosophy.

296
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,010
Please, have a taste.

297
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:02,860
It goes down smooth.

298
00:22:03,490 --> 00:22:06,030
Of course,
you have a refined palate.

299
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:07,830
It's not that my taste is better.

300
00:22:07,830 --> 00:22:09,330
Everyone else's just isn't
as sharp anymore.

301
00:22:09,970 --> 00:22:11,870
People are always eating spicy,
salty, or sweet foods,

302
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,940
constantly searching
for stronger flavors.

303
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:16,970
A drink that captures
the true essence of water.

304
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:21,910
It helps our bodies find balance,
even with our modern, intense diets.

305
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:24,080
It's a great fit...

306
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:27,320
for your "balanced diet" concept
this season.

307
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:33,620
I've revised my proposal too.

308
00:22:33,820 --> 00:22:35,660
Once you see the larger budget,

309
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:38,860
I'm sure that unfortunate incident
will be forgotten.

310
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:42,230
I'll take a look.

311
00:22:43,330 --> 00:22:44,840
I'll be in touch
after I've reviewed them.

312
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:02,220
You said you'd help me,
but you were lying, weren't you?

313
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:05,320
You seemed awfully sincere,
the way you were trying...

314
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:06,960
to win over Producer Shin.

315
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:09,990
Really? I was barely even trying.

316
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:14,330
If I'd really been trying,
he would've signed on the spot.

317
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:15,800
What?

318
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:19,200
Are you really trying
to pick a fight with me?

319
00:23:20,540 --> 00:23:22,140
You still don't trust me?

320
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:27,580
Yesterday, I told the chairman
I was ready to quit.

321
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:30,610
President Kim and Chairman Park
are the ones...

322
00:23:30,610 --> 00:23:31,980
who wanted me to compete.

323
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:36,390
You and Oh Jung Ran are the ones
who complicated things.

324
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:41,160
If you'd just stayed out of it,

325
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:44,330
I would've made sure
you won gracefully.

326
00:23:45,030 --> 00:23:47,600
But now there are
too many eyes on us,

327
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:50,470
so I have to act
like I'm trying hard.

328
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:53,840
So?

329
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:56,370
What's your plan, then?

330
00:23:57,240 --> 00:24:01,010
I've prepared a trump card
to make sure you win.

331
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:05,780
We'll pretend to compete,
but in the end, you'll win the deal.

332
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:10,390
So don't drag anyone else into this
and complicate things.

333
00:24:11,390 --> 00:24:12,390
This is so frustrating.

334
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,790
Should I trust her,
or just blow this whole thing up?

335
00:24:17,830 --> 00:24:21,570
You're probably anxious,
wondering if you can trust me.

336
00:24:22,330 --> 00:24:25,440
That anxiety will be your undoing.

337
00:24:25,940 --> 00:24:30,670
And the more anxious you get,
the more fun my next card will be.

338
00:24:40,620 --> 00:24:43,950
I just wanted to see him briefly.
Where on earth is he?

339
00:24:44,990 --> 00:24:48,930
I wonder if he took his medicine.
I need to check on his injury.

340
00:24:49,390 --> 00:24:51,390
This is making my blood boil.

341
00:24:52,030 --> 00:24:54,970
- This is all that vixen's fault.
- Enough!

342
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:58,870
Stop calling her that.

343
00:25:00,170 --> 00:25:02,710
Why are you raising your voice
at me too?

344
00:25:02,770 --> 00:25:05,640
It's because
you keep insulting Chloe...

345
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:09,780
Actually, it's because you insulted
Hyun Jun's feelings for her...

346
00:25:09,780 --> 00:25:12,050
that he went so far
as to hurt himself.

347
00:25:12,150 --> 00:25:13,980
You think I enjoy this?

348
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:16,890
I'm only doing this
because I'm afraid she'll ruin her life.

349
00:25:16,890 --> 00:25:18,790
- Just stop it.
- Stop what?

350
00:25:18,890 --> 00:25:21,090
He's so crazy about her.

351
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,760
Don't get all serious on me.

352
00:25:29,930 --> 00:25:31,000
What's up?

353
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:32,540
Are you here to see me?

354
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:35,170
I'm on my way
to Director Park Min Jun's office.

355
00:25:37,170 --> 00:25:41,780
The bio division has to share
all proposals with him.

356
00:25:42,180 --> 00:25:44,810
I handed mine
to Producer Shin today.

357
00:25:48,020 --> 00:25:49,090
Hyun Jun.

358
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:50,650
Hyun Jun, you...

359
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:55,230
What... Hey!

360
00:25:56,430 --> 00:25:58,330
What are you doing? Let go.

361
00:25:58,330 --> 00:25:59,930
- Hey!
- Just stop.

362
00:26:01,700 --> 00:26:03,970
Leave him be.

363
00:26:06,140 --> 00:26:07,900
(Division 2 Director's Office)

364
00:26:14,480 --> 00:26:16,980
What happened to your hand?

365
00:26:19,050 --> 00:26:20,050
This?

366
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:22,150
I was arguing with my mom and...

367
00:26:25,390 --> 00:26:27,320
There was just
no getting through to her,

368
00:26:29,330 --> 00:26:30,590
so I had to make a point
with my actions.

369
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:34,700
Even so,

370
00:26:35,330 --> 00:26:37,700
you shouldn't resort
to hurting yourself.

371
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:39,500
Well,

372
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,570
it's not all bad.

373
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:44,980
Now I have your full attention,

374
00:26:45,540 --> 00:26:46,810
and you're even worried about me.

375
00:26:55,050 --> 00:26:58,720
(Head of Division 1, Park Min Jun)

376
00:26:58,790 --> 00:27:01,560
(Head of Division 1, Park Min Jun)

377
00:27:02,260 --> 00:27:03,530
(Explosion incident)

378
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:10,330
(Fingerprint Restoration)

379
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,470
(Prioritizing evidence before
estimating the ignition point)

380
00:27:15,540 --> 00:27:18,040
(Experiment: Restoring fingerprints
from explosion site evidence)

381
00:27:24,710 --> 00:27:28,620
Hello, Professor.
I'm Park Min Jun of Adele Group.

382
00:27:29,820 --> 00:27:33,260
I'm calling to ask
about your research paper.

383
00:27:34,660 --> 00:27:37,060
Would you be available
to meet right away?

384
00:27:45,170 --> 00:27:47,000
Let's just pay him off.

385
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:50,170
What if meeting him
complicates things?

386
00:27:51,110 --> 00:27:54,740
If we sweep this under the rug,
it'll only get worse.

387
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:58,380
For now, I need to meet him
and figure out a solution.

388
00:27:58,750 --> 00:28:00,320
Where are you going to meet him?

389
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:04,550
If you need to meet in secret,
should we ask to use Ihwachae again?

390
00:28:15,530 --> 00:28:16,600
It's me.

391
00:28:17,630 --> 00:28:20,040
Why'd you leave me hanging
after making me wait?

392
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,910
That's why I came here myself.

393
00:28:23,670 --> 00:28:26,580
I'm in the office lobby.
Find us a place to talk, now.

394
00:28:27,710 --> 00:28:28,950
Try standing me up again.

395
00:28:29,910 --> 00:28:31,410
I swear I won't let it slide.

396
00:28:39,690 --> 00:28:42,860
What now?
He got impatient and came here.

397
00:28:43,730 --> 00:28:47,060
At this point, it might be better
to just face him head-on.

398
00:28:48,570 --> 00:28:49,570
Tell him to come up.

399
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:02,880
It's been years,
but I'd know that face anywhere.

400
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:04,350
Of course.

401
00:29:04,750 --> 00:29:07,820
You're her.
The Kim Dan Hui my uncle adopted.

402
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:11,520
After my uncle adopted you,
I heard you were in the hospital...

403
00:29:11,820 --> 00:29:13,160
for a long time.

404
00:29:13,590 --> 00:29:16,290
But you were ungrateful
for his kindness...

405
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:18,460
and just ran away,
cutting off all contact.

406
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:22,470
It's about time
you repaid our family for raising you.

407
00:29:23,670 --> 00:29:27,840
If you're a chairman's mistress,
you must be loaded.

408
00:29:28,370 --> 00:29:30,640
Hold on.
Who are you calling a mistress?

409
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:31,880
It's okay, Secretary Jung.

410
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:38,010
Sir, I believe
you have the wrong person.

411
00:29:38,750 --> 00:29:42,820
I'm not Kim Dan Hui.
My name is Kim Myung Hui.

412
00:29:43,490 --> 00:29:47,160
Right. I thought
something was off at first, too.

413
00:29:48,630 --> 00:29:49,630
You must've changed your name.

414
00:29:50,690 --> 00:29:52,500
I'm Kim Myung Hui, sir.

415
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:56,700
I see.
You're going to play dumb, are you?

416
00:29:58,030 --> 00:30:01,800
What, do I have to bring you a copy
of your family records?

417
00:30:02,410 --> 00:30:03,910
By all means, bring them.

418
00:30:04,610 --> 00:30:07,840
I'll get my official registration
to prove I'm Kim Myung Hui.

419
00:30:09,780 --> 00:30:12,250
If your proof is conclusive,

420
00:30:12,580 --> 00:30:15,950
you'll get the money
you think you're owed.

421
00:30:17,950 --> 00:30:18,960
Proof?

422
00:30:20,990 --> 00:30:22,030
That's rich.

423
00:30:24,130 --> 00:30:25,300
I'm the proof.

424
00:30:25,930 --> 00:30:27,730
My memory is the proof.

425
00:30:27,730 --> 00:30:29,100
If you make accusations...

426
00:30:29,630 --> 00:30:32,470
and demand money without proof,

427
00:30:33,570 --> 00:30:34,570
I'll have...

428
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:37,610
no choice but to take legal action.

429
00:30:39,510 --> 00:30:40,510
Legal action?

430
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:42,680
Legal action?

431
00:30:47,450 --> 00:30:48,690
You wait right here.

432
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:53,260
I'll be back
with that "proof" you like so much,

433
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:54,520
so just wait.

434
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:03,430
He really is the nephew
of your adoptive parents, isn't he?

435
00:31:04,130 --> 00:31:05,240
Yes.

436
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,100
Can you really afford
to just let him go like that?

437
00:31:08,740 --> 00:31:09,870
If I show any weakness,

438
00:31:10,570 --> 00:31:12,910
he'll latch on and won't let go.

439
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:17,850
First, I need to see
what cards he's holding.

440
00:31:19,780 --> 00:31:20,780
That's true.

441
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:23,020
Officially, Kim Dan Hui is dead,

442
00:31:23,390 --> 00:31:25,690
and you've been Kim Myung Hui
for the last 30 years.

443
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:29,330
So unless he brings solid proof,
we have the upper hand.

444
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:41,770
Darn it.

445
00:31:42,370 --> 00:31:45,170
I talked a big game,
and now she wants proof?

446
00:31:46,580 --> 00:31:49,450
After my uncle died,
all his stuff was likely thrown out.

447
00:31:50,510 --> 00:31:51,850
Seriously.

448
00:31:53,620 --> 00:31:55,790
She's not Kim Myung Hui.
She's Kim Dan Hui.

449
00:31:56,290 --> 00:31:57,290
How do I prove it?

450
00:31:59,460 --> 00:32:00,460
Hold on.

451
00:32:08,500 --> 00:32:09,970
What did you just say?

452
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:14,740
She's Kim Dan Hui,
not Kim Myung Hui?

453
00:32:50,210 --> 00:32:53,040
(Pearl in Red)

454
00:32:53,410 --> 00:32:56,150
This is one of the personal effects
from the car explosion?

455
00:32:56,250 --> 00:32:58,610
Yes, but it's been seven years
since the explosion.

456
00:32:58,610 --> 00:32:59,980
Would there be any prints left?

457
00:33:00,050 --> 00:33:01,220
I'll do my best.

458
00:33:01,220 --> 00:33:03,950
Kim Myung Hui, no, Kim Dan Hui.

459
00:33:04,250 --> 00:33:06,560
She's been tricking all of us.

460
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:08,520
What are you talking about?

461
00:33:08,890 --> 00:33:12,600
Myung Hui, answer me.
What is this all about?

462
00:33:14,260 --> 00:33:16,270
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
